cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.DL 

The paper focuses on the evaluation of interaction with technologies where notations are created and used by various people, or by a single person in various, and potentially distant, occasions. This suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) due to the mention of data-intensive applications. Additionally, the paper mentions a computer tool that supports qualitative data analysis, which could fall under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL).
